rom course-manager roles — they should not have course-level read access by design.\",\"scope\":\"LMS role model\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-17T20:39:05.717Z","wordCount":498,"positions":[2,10,19,32,39,48,55,61,69,80,88,102,119,126,137,147,154,164,177,183,190,203,219,232,240,245,253,260,272,279,292,299,328,337,344,350,358,376,390,397,405,425,434,441,447,452,462,472,480,484,489]},"ep_stage_diary_002":{"taskId":"fix-pr-1266-260417-202804","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_002","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review-fix\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"decision\",\"text\":\"Adding a clarifying comment is a valid fix when the behavior is correct by design but not self-explanatory to future readers.\",\"scope\":\"code review\"},{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"AdvancedContentEditor is an exercise-editor role, not a course-manager role — intentionally excluded from instructor list read access.\",\"scope\":\"LMS/permissions\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"When fixing review feedback, prefer the minimal appropriate solution rather than over-engineering.\",\"scope\":\"PR workflow\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-17T21:21:41.525Z","wordCount":548,"positions":[2,10,17,23,36,43,54,61,70,81,94,100,113,125,136,147,151,156,171,178,189,197,202,213,220,229,236,264,273,280,286,292,299,307,314,328,342,353,358,363,373,381,385,401,408,417,429,436,443,453,464,472,484,493,500,505,510,525,533,536]},"ep_stage_diary_003":{"taskId":"fix-pr-1266-260418-070628","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_003","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"Code with surprising exclusions (like AdvancedContentEditor from read access) should include a clarifying comment at the exclusion site explaining the design rationale, not just the intent.\",\"scope\":\"auth\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"Multi-pass structured review (CRI-Triage → CRI-Detail → CRII-Context → CRIII-Holistic) catches both correctness issues and design-rationale gaps that single-pass reviews miss.\",\"scope\":\"code-review\"},{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"Without an inline comment at the exclusion site itself, reviewers cannot distinguish intentional design from accidental omission — always comment the 'why' at the decision point.\",\"scope\":\"auth\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-18T07:33:14.490Z","wordCount":713,"positions":[2,10,19,32,39,52,59,69,80,92,97,124,129,144,154,165,180,190,195,210,217,228,232,241,251,259,268,275,284,291,297,302,313,321,325,334,338,347,352,362,368,378,386,391,403,414,421,431,441,448,453,461,469,477,482,493,500,509,516,527,534,549,559,564,572,582,589,601,613,625,636,647,654,679,688,697,705]},"ep_review_001":{"taskId":"fix-pr-1266-260418-070628","episodeId":"ep_review_001","source":"review","content":"I now have a complete picture of the PR. Here is the structured review.\n\n---\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Summary\n\nPR #1266 implements the Instructor role and per-course permissions for the LMS. The primary change is a clarifying comment in `CourseInstructors.ts` (lines 98–99) explaining why `AdvancedContentEditor` is intentionally excluded from read access — resolving the sole open item from the previous Kody review. Supporting infrastructure includes the `CourseInstructors` collection, `instructorAccess.ts` helpers, and the `/api/instructor/gradebook/[courseId]` endpoint.\n\n## Findings\n\n### Critical\nNone.\n\n### Major\nNone.\n\n### Minor\nNone — the previously flagged minor item (missing design-rationale comment) is now resolved at `CourseInstructors.ts:98–99`.\n\n---\n\n## Two-Pass Review\n\n**Pass 1 — CRITICAL:**\n\n### SQL & Data Safety\nAll queries use Payload's parameterized `where` clauses (`equals`, `in` operators). No string interpolation in queries. The gradebook route uses `enrolledUsers.docs.map","createdAt":"2026-04-18T07:33:14.509Z","wordCount":1000,"positions":[2,13,22,37,41,53,64,81,90,99,108,112,117,132,143,152,156,163,183,192,200,212,223,235,253,258,264,267,271,287,313,327,341,346,355,369,374,379,393,402,407,415,426,441,455,474,487,504,508,527,531,542,553,564,578,592,601,612,618,629,635,646,657,665,671,677,685,692,702,714,718,731,749,752,755,769,773,778,788,797,814,820,825,836,844,848,858,880,890,904,916,919,926,943,956,966,972,978,992,997]},"ep_stage_diary_004":{"taskId":"fix-pr-1266-260418-070628","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_004","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review-fix\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"Document intentional security exclusions in comments near the exclusion logic, explaining why access is denied rather than granted — this resolves ambiguity during review.\",\"scope\":\"src/payload/collections/CourseInstructors.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"LMS access control uses a dedicated helper file (instructorAccess.ts) rather than inlining permissions, keeping collection configs clean and reusable.\",\"scope\":\"src/payload/access/instructorAccess.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"AdvancedContentEditor must be explicitly excluded from read access in instructor permissions; omitting this exclusion silently grants broader read access than intended.\",\"scope\":\"LMS instructor permissions\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-18T07:35:53.655Z","wordCount":753,"positions":[2,10,17,23,36,43,52,59,68,80,89,103,112,121,131,138,153,163,170,177,182,197,206,216,223,233,241,245,253,265,283,290,297,310,317,321,328,336,343,353,360,366,383,387,394,399,408,421,429,440,448,458,470,478,482,490,497,514,521,528,537,544,566,574,585,599,604,614,625,638,652,662,671,678,686,691,698,703,715,723,727,738]}},"totalDocs":5}